Set::strings()-&gt;chars();
</code></pre> <p>This describes any chars that can be returned by the <code>\chr()</code> function.</p> <pre><code>use Innmind\BlackBox\Set;

Set::strings()-&gt;chars()-&gt;lowercaseLetter();
</code></pre> <p>This describes the range <code>a..z</code>.</p> <pre><code>use Innmind\BlackBox\Set;

Set::strings()-&gt;chars()-&gt;uppercaseLetter();
</code></pre> <p>This describes the range <code>A..Z</code>.</p> <pre><code>use Innmind\BlackBox\Set;

